---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Learn | Manopause"
  description="Educational resources to understand relationship conflict, abuse, trauma responses, and how to build healthier patterns."
>
  <main class="learn-page">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>Learn</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">
          Understanding is the first step toward change. Explore research-backed 
          information about relationship patterns, trauma, and the path to healthier dynamics.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="container content-wrapper">
      
      <!-- Introduction -->
      <section class="intro">
        <p>
          When you're in the middle of relationship conflict, it can be hard to see 
          clearly. These educational resources are designed to help you understand 
          what's happening, why patterns repeat, and what options you have.
        </p>
        <p>
          Take your time. There's no rush. Read what feels relevant to you right now.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Article Grid -->
      <section class="article-grid">
        
        <a href="/learn/what-is-abuse" class="article-card">
          <div class="article-icon">‚ö†Ô∏è</div>
          <div class="article-content">
            <h2>What Is Abuse?</h2>
            <p class="read-time">8 min read</p>
            <p class="description">
              Abuse isn't just physical. Learn about emotional, psychological, and 
              coercive control ‚Äî and how to distinguish unhealthy conflict from abuse.
            </p>
            <span class="learn-more">Read article ‚Üí</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/learn/trauma-responses" class="article-card">
          <div class="article-icon">üß†</div>
          <div class="article-content">
            <h2>Trauma & Stress Responses</h2>
            <p class="read-time">12 min read</p>
            <p class="description">
              Fight, flight, freeze, fawn ‚Äî how your nervous system responds to threat, 
              and why understanding this helps you respond more intentionally.
            </p>
            <span class="learn-more">Read article ‚Üí</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/learn/patterns" class="article-card">
          <div class="article-icon">üîÑ</div>
          <div class="article-content">
            <h2>Patterns Library</h2>
            <p class="read-time">20 min read</p>
            <p class="description">
              A comprehensive guide to recognizing harmful relationship patterns ‚Äî from 
              accusations and monitoring to isolation and financial control.
            </p>
            <span class="learn-more">Explore patterns ‚Üí</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/learn/hormones" class="article-card">
          <div class="article-icon">‚öóÔ∏è</div>
          <div class="article-content">
            <h2>Hormones & Behavior</h2>
            <p class="read-time">16 min read</p>
            <p class="description">
              How hormonal changes in both men and women can affect mood, behavior, and 
              relationships ‚Äî and when to consider medical evaluation.
            </p>
            <span class="learn-more">Read article ‚Üí</span>
          </div>
        </a>

      </section>

      <!-- Quick Distinctions -->
      <section class="quick-info">
        <h2>Quick Distinctions</h2>
        
        <div class="distinction-grid">
          <div class="distinction-card">
            <h3>Normal Conflict vs. Abuse</h3>
            <div class="comparison">
              <div class="side normal">
                <h4>Normal Conflict</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Both people can express concerns</li>
                  <li>Disagreements get resolved</li>
                  <li>Respect remains even when upset</li>
                  <li>You feel safe to disagree</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="side concern">
                <h4>Concerning Patterns</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>One person dominates discussions</li>
                  <li>Same issues cycle without resolution</li>
                  <li>Contempt, control, or intimidation</li>
                  <li>Fear prevents honest expression</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="distinction-card">
            <h3>Explanation vs. Excuse</h3>
            <p>
              Understanding why someone behaves a certain way (stress, hormones, trauma) 
              is not the same as excusing harmful behavior. Reasons help us understand; 
              they don't remove responsibility.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Navigation Help -->
      <section class="nav-help">
        <h2>Where Should I Start?</h2>
        
        <div class="help-grid">
          <div class="help-card">
            <h3>I'm not sure what's happening</h3>
            <p>Start with <a href="/start-here">the assessment</a> to get personalized guidance.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="help-card">
            <h3>I think I might be experiencing abuse</h3>
            <p>Read <a href="/learn/what-is-abuse">What Is Abuse?</a> to understand the patterns.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="help-card">
            <h3>I'm constantly on edge</h3>
            <p>Explore <a href="/learn/trauma-responses">Trauma & Stress Responses</a> to understand why.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="help-card">
            <h3>I need practical help now</h3>
            <p>Check out our <a href="/tools">Tools section</a> for actionable strategies.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Disclaimer -->
      <section class="disclaimer-section">
        <h2>A Note on This Content</h2>
        <p>
          All content in this section is educational and based on research from reputable 
          sources including the CDC, National Domestic Violence Hotline, and peer-reviewed 
          research. We summarize findings in plain language and encourage you to explore 
          our <a href="/references">References page</a> for sources.
        </p>
        <p>
          This information is not a substitute for professional help. If you need support, 
          please reach out to a qualified professional or contact a <a href="/get-help">crisis resource</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .learn-page {
    --primary: #2563eb;
    --secondary: #7c3aed;
  }

  .hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1e293b 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 4rem 1rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .content-wrapper {
    padding: 3rem 1rem;
  }

  .intro {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .intro p {
    color: #475569;
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto 1rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  /* Article Grid */
  .article-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(350px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .article-card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    background: white;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .article-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-3px);
    box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    border-color: var(--primary);
  }

  .article-icon {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .article-content h2 {
    color: #1e293b;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .read-time {
    color: var(--primary);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .description {
    color: #64748b;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .learn-more {
    color: var(--primary);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  /* Quick Info */
  .quick-info {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .quick-info h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #1e293b;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .distinction-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .distinction-card {
    background: #f8fafc;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
  }

  .distinction-card h3 {
    color: #1e293b;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .distinction-card > p {
    color: #475569;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .comparison {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .side {
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
  }

  .side.normal {
    background: #ecfdf5;
    border: 1px solid #a7f3d0;
  }

  .side.concern {
    background: #fef2f2;
    border: 1px solid #fecaca;
  }

  .side h4 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .side.normal h4 { color: #065f46; }
  .side.concern h4 { color: #991b1b; }

  .side ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .side li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .side.normal li { color: #047857; }
  .side.concern li { color: #b91c1c; }

  /* Nav Help */
  .nav-help {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .nav-help h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #1e293b;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .help-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .help-card {
    background: white;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
  }

  .help-card h3 {
    color: #334155;
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .help-card p {
    color: #64748b;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .help-card a {
    color: var(--primary);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  /* Disclaimer */
  .disclaimer-section {
    background: #fffbeb;
    border: 1px solid #fcd34d;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .disclaimer-section h2 {
    color: #92400e;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .disclaimer-section p {
    color: #a16207;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .disclaimer-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .disclaimer-section a {
    color: #b45309;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }

    .article-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .article-card {
      flex-direction: column;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .comparison {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
